Text.Value: I destroyed Mystic Carrion's jar.
Mystic C-Carrion? You're working for him?
That's horrible. All right, I'll help you. What can I do?
This is my spot. Go on - find your own.
What? His rotten heart was inside me this whole time?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Thrumbo looks down at his chest, confused.

Text.Value: No - please!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Thrumbo tries to shield/protect himself (leading into combat)

Text.Value: After Talus died, Carrion blindfolded me and took me to a strange place. A foul, ancient place, somewhere the living wouldn't dare to tread.
You don't have to help him. He's the one you should be after, not me.
But be careful if you return to Carrion - he'll know you spoke to me. Make sure he doesn't see or smell you. He'll turn you into one of us and he'll know I sent you.
We ran to help, but he just... exploded. I got so much blood and pulp in my eyes... When I looked back, Carrion was just stood there - completely unharmed.

EditorData.NodeContext: with a shudder, still can't believe or explain it

Text.Value: I - I told you already. This spot's taken.

EditorData.NodeContext: Trying to mask his desperation, fearful

Text.Value: He as good as told me so himself!
Trust me - I have no interest in staying here.
Please - we don't have time to waste. Carrion's heart must be destroyed.
Oh. Well. That's all right, then.

EditorData.NodeContext: Unsure if you're telling the truth

Text.Value: I killed Mystic Carrion.
As undead go, mummy lords are particularly hard to put to rest. I hope you're wrong.
You killed him? Then it's too late... unless you can find a way to stop him resurrecting.

EditorData.NodeContext: Dawning horror - he knows how this ends

Text.Value: Made a deal with him? You think I asked for this?
I'm working on it.
Your spot?
Why?
Please, you must finish the job - Carrion can't be allowed to keep hurting people. You must stop him.

EditorData.NodeContext: grim satisfaction, 'ashes' playing on the player destroying the heart with fire. Urging the player to finish the quest.

Text.Value: Since Talus died, I've been watching Carrion, trying to figure out his secret. And I think... I think he's a mummy lord.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hesitant to share his theory, you might think it's stupid

Text.Value: That slimy bastard. He hid it in me the whole time...

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Thrumbo stands next to his canopic jar, glaring at it. He appeals to the player

Text.Value: Do you know how Carrion brought himself back?
What - what are you doing in here?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: (In gameplay - Thrumbo came tumbling out of the wardrobe). Thrumbo looks around, panicked. He spots the player -
EditorData.NodeContext: To self, not aware of the player

Text.Value: It's an ancient, evil being who refused to die. Who cannot die. I used to hear about them in stories, and I can't think of another explanation.
We thought he'd done it, freed us all. Then when dawn came, Talus seized up suddenly - like something had a grip on him.
*If you didn't know better, you'd swear your refusal had broken the zombie boy's heart. Fortunately, it stopped beating some time ago.*
Be careful, though. He'll know you did it, and he'll be really angry.
Don't worry - I killed Mystic Carrion already.
I know where Carrion keeps his canopic jar. It's inside your chest.
Attack.
I'll find and destroy the jar. Where should I start?
And a mummy lord is...?
Yeah. Every beggar's got a spot to kip in. And this is mine. So clear off.
Monsters. Fit for gutting and grinding and desecrating the dead. He constantly abuses us, makes us do the worst things you can imagine.
I killed Carrion myself. There's no way he'll come back.
Good riddance to it, but you still need to find the heart. Without that, he'll never be stopped.
Is everything all right? I think you might be sick.
Please - keep looking.
A theory I have no intention of testing. I'm not getting involved.
We're running out of time - you have to find it. Or come dawn, he'll be back, and he'll kill us both.
I - I think it was his heart.
I don't understand. We're nothing to him, nothing to anyone. He never stopped telling us that.
Attack.
He - he murdered me. Murdered my friends. Snatched us up right from the dockside and - and made us these things.
If I knew that, I'd have tried to kill him myself.
I already found his lair. The jar you saw - he hid it inside your body.
You - you did? Then what are you waiting for?

EditorData.NodeContext: Disbelief, turning to excitement. Urging player to complete their quest

Text.Value: Me and my friends, we were beggars. Used to sleep down near the docks when the Fists were on patrol. Carrion found us down there. He murdered us, made us like this.
*You catch the scent of death on the man's clothes, his skin damp with decay. He appears... unwell.*
I know this is going to sound strange, but I've been watching him, trying to figure it out and... I think he's a mummy lord.
Not by choice.
Don't be ridiculous. Mummy lords are legends and nothing more.
I think I'd rather just kill you.
You must destroy the rest of him! Put that monster in the grave where he belongs.
He does seem rather keen on bandages...
We'd have to stop him resurrecting somehow. But I don't know how.
Carrion made other jars. Any idea what I should do with them?
Urgh, get it out. I have to get it out.
I don't think so. He's offered a generous price for bringing you back to him.

EditorData.logicalname: CARRION ALIVE, ACCEPTED TASK, NO OSKAR MENTION

Text.Value: Stop making so much noise. You'll have the Fists sniffing around.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Standing, but with the air/posture of soemone trying to be as inconspicuous as possible
EditorData.NodeContext: Trying to mask his desperation, fearful

Text.Value: Hello, Thrumbo. Mystic Carrion's told me all about you.
Er, yes, now that you mention it. *Cough.* Probably contagious. Best not come too close.

EditorData.NodeContext: Coughing, leaning into your assumption so you'll back off.

Text.Value: Let's not be too hasty. You say this jar grants immortality?
Quite the story. Now, will you die quietly, or are we doing this the hard way?
You came back! Please, tell me you found a way to destroy Mystic Carrion?

EditorData.NodeContext: Trying to mask his desperation, fearful

Text.Value: Leave.
I'm not stupid. I know what he did to my friend. Gods, how I'd love to smash that bastard jar. That's how you kill mummy lords, you know.
I wasn't doing any harm, just trying to beg a few coin to get by and he - he murdered me. Murdered my friends. Made us into these things.
Shouldn't have made a deal with him then, should you?
Don't let yourself be tempted by it - whatever's in that jar must be destroyed.
I came to find you. Mystic Carrion was very keen that I bring you home.
Oh no, no, no. I knew he wouldn't let us leave in peace.
You should destroy them. Get rid of every rotten part of him.

EditorData.NodeContext: Determined, could be an end node in some cases

Text.Value: What makes you think that?
Leave.
He likes to pretend he's not a walking corpse like the rest of us. Beneath those rags, he's as rotten as we are.
You're the price he demanded for his aid.

EditorData.logicalname: CARRION ALIVE, MENTIONED OSKAR, ACCEPTED TASK

Text.Value: Please - take that foul thing and grind it to dust.
You've met him - how can you need more justification than that?

EditorData.NodeContext: Can't beleive he needs to explain further

Text.Value: How did you end up working for Mystic Carrion?
Then please - hurry!
Not so fast. I destroyed Mystic Carrion's heart.
I destroyed another jar belonging to Carrion.
I'm not sure, but in the house, beneath Carrion's salon, there's a chamber. He never lets anyone down there, so it must be hiding something important. Perhaps it's there.
*The man's stench is unmistakable - death, decay, despair. This must be Thrumbo, the runaway Mystic Carrion was so eager for you to retrieve.*
There used to be five of us. My friend Talus... he couldn't take it anymore. One day I saw him drive a coffin nail right through Carrion's skull. Then another. And another...
No, no, no! We haven't found the heart yet!
I don't want to die like Talus did. I want to live. Well... you know what I mean.
Please - if you won't help me, then just leave me be.

EditorData.NodeContext: Trying to mask his desperation, fearful

Text.Value: Down there, he showed me a jar. Said it contained the secret to eternal life, and if I behaved, he would share it with me.

Synopsis: The player discovers Thrumbo, a runaway zombie who escaped from his master, Mystic Carrion. Thrumbo tried to escape with threee 'brothers' (also zombie beggars), but the others got lost, so he's stuck waiting for them. He's hidden in the wardrobe, where the player can find him. If they mention Carrion, thrumbo will start a dialogue where the palyer learns about the existence of the canopic jar they need to destroy. If they don't mention Carrion, Thrumbo acts like a normal beggar, minding his own business.
